SIMPLE: honorably
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honorably
<hw>Hon"or*a*bly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In
an honorable manner; in a manner showing, or consistent with,
honor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The reverend abbot . . . <qex>honorably</qex> received him.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why did I not more <qex>honorably</qex> starve?</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Decently; becomingly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Do this message <xex>honorably</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Magnanimously; generously; nobly; worthily;
justly; equitably; fairly; reputably.</syn></p>

<p><ent>Honorary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Honorarium</ent>⟦br⟧
